name: The Ambient Visitor - One Two
description: The first two albums from my side project The Ambient Visitor, remixed, remastered and extended. Two longform ambient albums on two vinyl style CDs with an art insert in a slim card case. More from The Ambient Visitor: theambientvisitor.com

name: Solar EP
description: More info / preview / download: www.bingsatellites.com/releases/solar/ The first in a series of EPs available on mini CD and download. This EP was originally available as a bonus item but is now available separately. Please note - because of postage costs, I suggest buying this CD with another item. Outside of the UK, stand alone postage is nearly as much as the cost of the EP, whereas if you buy it as an additional item, the additional postage will be a fraction of that cost. All music written performed and produced by Bing Satellites at MCos, Manchester, February - July 2013

name: Mostly Ambient Radio Sessions September 2013
description: Listen to the album at www.bingsatellites.com/september The new album of live performances by Bing Satellites, broadcast on www.radiosunrise.de and radio.electro-music.com during September 2013. Over 3 and a half hours of improvised ambient and electronic music available on a 4 CD package and download. Included in this performances is a an experiment at recording and layering improvised piano loops live. For the first time in a while, there is guitar that actually sounds like a guitar and I sing - yes, that's right! You have been warned! The CD version of this album includes some extra music and comes in a newly designed 4 CD package - 4 vinyl style CDs with an 8 page booklet in a slim card case. This package is about the same size and weight as a single CD in a normal jewel case but holds 4 CDs! This means postage is a lot less than it would have been with a normal 4 CD package. And, even if I say so myself, it looks rather nice too.

name: Bing Satellites & Daniel Land - King Midas In Reverse
description: Out now! The brand new collaboration between myself and Daniel Land. An album of quiet, beautiful songs performed on piano and guitar. This album started life at a riverrun concert myself and Daniel performed in Manchester. During that concert we performed a track using a processed piano and guitar. We liked it a lot and decided then to make an album based around piano and guitar. We started working on this album in January 2013 during sessions for Daniel's next solo album. We worked very quickly. It soon became apparent that we had something special on our hands - and something we are both very proud of. We are both fans of the paintings of artist Ade Hodges, so much so that the album is named after the painting which forms the album cover. You can find more of the paintings of Ade Hodges at www.facebook.com/adehodgesartist More details / preview can be found at www.bfwrecordings.com/midas

name: Soothing Images 1-15
description: 15 quiet ambient songs with 15 accompanying photographs. 2 CDs plus a 20 page booklet featuring all the music and artwork from the album. How the music is created: A 16 bar phrase is played. That phrase is fed into a slowly decaying 16 bar loop, similar to the one used in Twilight Sessions. That loop is fed into a slowly decaying 6 bar loop which repeates the first loop every 6 bars, so that soon, there are several layers of the original phrase that interact and create new themes and melodies. They seem to appear from nowhere, but these new melodies are destined to happen as soon as each note is played in the original 16 bar phrase. More details and preview at www.bingsatellites.com/releases/soothingimages1-15/

name: Twilight Sessions volume 11
description: An album of peaceful ambient music. Over 2 hours of chilled ambient on double CD or download. Listen at www.bingsatellites.com/releases/twilightsessionsvolume11 Well, it is finally here. Nearly ten months after volume 10, comes the eleventh volume on the Twilight Sessions series. Recorded during April and May 2013, the album is a collection of quiet, improvised ambient songs performed on guitar (a fair bit of ebow too), piano and my usual selection of synths. It is the first Twilight Sessions album to be released on CD. The previous albums will be released on CD over the next few months. The music is played into a long, slowly decaying loop. These loops are quite long (often around 90 seconds or more) and with very little rhythm to speak of, it is difficult to know precisely where I am in the loop, so I can add notes and sounds where I see fit, but can never know exactly what I am adding these notes to. Therefore, it must be said that although I am the one making these sounds and creating this music, much of it is down to serendipity. More Twilight Sessions:

name: Live in Salford & Manchester
description:
An album capturing the very first solo Bing Satellites concert.

Tracks 1-3 recorded during rehearsals at MCos, Manchester, 4th May 2013

Tracks 4-6 recorded during my debut live performance at Buried Bones @ The New Oxford - part of Sounds From The Other City 2013, a festival of new music in Salford, UK. 
Many thanks to Buried Bones for inviting me. 

All the music on this album is completely improvised. 
I start with a note or two and see where the music takes me.

The music was performed on laptop and midi keyboard (using Reason and Ableton Live) and guitar (mainly played with an ebow).

The cover art is derived from a satellite image showing the locations of these recording.

name: Centuries
description: My second CD release is an album of chilled ambience. Recorded at my home studio from April 2012 to February 2013, the album features music played on baritone guitar, piano and synths plus a ton of electronic jiggery pokery. The CD is housed in a beautiful, natural card package and includes a digital download of the album. There will be more CDs on the way soon. Orders will be shipped from 18 March 2013 onwards. More details: www.bingsatellites.com/centuries

name: Und
description: Listen at www.bingsatellites.com/releases/und Und is a special new release - 70 minutes of chilled ambient music on a limited edition CD and name-your-price download. Recorded at MCos, Manchester in February and March 2013. The music on this album was performed and recorded on a very minimal, basic set up - guitar, keyboard and laptop. This restriction really inspired me and I recorded a lot of music in this period. The music on this album was completely improvised.

name: Motif
description: Listen: http://www.bingsatellites.com/releases/motif Live music is a wonderful thing! During February and March 2013, I started rehearsing for my first public concert as Bing Satellites. I've performed live before but always as part of a band or what-have-you, or in the comfort of my home studio with lots of synths, guitars and other instruments close at hand. However, for these rehearsals, I tried to have as minimal a set up as possible - small enough to transport to gig venues but with the flexibility to produce a wide range of sounds. In the end, I settled on laptop and mixer, a small keyboard and my smallest guitar and I set these up in my living room, separate from the rest of my musical equipment. The result was an inspired and productive few weeks. I improvised and recorded hours and hours of new music, some of which you can hear on this and other albums. Although, all of this music was improvised, it appears I unknowingly started a few pieces with the same three notes (or variations on those three notes). I collected these pieces together on this album. Motif seemed a fitting name.

name: Visions & Memories
description: Price includes shipping worldwide. Ships from 20 September 2012. My very first CD release is a quiet album of drifting ambient music performed on piano, synth and baritone guitar. Recorded between March and August 2012. CD in beautifully designed cardboard wallet. tracklist: 1. Here it comes again 2. Another evening in slow motion 3. Light 4. Strange visions Total running time: 50:33 You can preview the whole album at www.bingsatellites.com

name: The Lovely Moon - Moonlight Drift
description: Listen at www.thelovelymoon.com/releases/moonlightdrift From one of my ambient side projects. 18 months in the making - it is finally here! Moonlight Drift is 75 minutes of peaceful ambient music, perfect for relaxing.

name: The Lovely Moon - Mostly Ambient Radio Sessions
description: Listen: www.thelovelymoon.com/releases/mostlyambientradiosessions A live album from one of my ambient side projects. An album of live, blissful ambient music. Late on 1st November, the first ever public performance by The Lovely Moon was broadcast live, as it happened on Bing Satellites Mostly Ambient Radio Show. More details: www.bingsatellites.com/radio This performance captures new live versions of songs from all three albums so far.

name: The Lovely Moon - Figures On The Beach
description: Listen: www.thelovelymoon.com/releases/figuresonthebeach An album from one of my ambient side projects. Our third album of peaceful ambient music. Recorded between March and October 2011. It features a new mix of 'sunlight through the trees' from eastern dreams, the full version of 'slomolomo' (the original version appears on the BFW recordings compilation Album In A Day volume 2, 'in the air' which originally appeared on Album In A Day volume 3, as well as four completely new tracks.
